{"title_page": "Rainbow (1978 film)", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Rainbow\n| image                = \n| caption              = \n| genre                = Biography<br>Drama<br>Music\n| based_on             = ''Rainbow: The Stormy Life of Judy Garland'' by Christopher Finch\n| writer               = [[John McGreevey]]\n| director             = [[Jackie Cooper]]\n| starring             = [[Andrea McArdle]]<br>[[Don Murray (actor)|Don Murray]]<br>[[Michael Parks]]<br>[[Piper Laurie]]<br>[[Rue McClanahan]]\n| music                = [[Charles Fox (composer)|Charles Fox]]\n| country              = United States\n| language             = English\n| executive_producer   = Greg Strangis<br>[[William Hogan (author)|William Hogan]]\n| producer             = Peter Dunne\n| editor               = Jerry Dronsky\n| cinematography       = Howard Schwartz\n| location             = \n| runtime              = 97 minutes\n| company              = Ten-Four Productions\n| distributor          = [[NBC]]\n| network              = NBC\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|1978|11|06}}\n| website              = \n}}\n'''''Rainbow''''' is a 1978 American [[television film|made-for-television]] [[biographical film|biographical]] [[musical film|musical]] [[drama (film and television)|drama film]] which chronicles the early years of singer-actress [[Judy Garland]], portrayed by [[Andrea McArdle]]. Directed by [[Jackie Cooper]], it was written by [[John McGreevey]] based on the 1975 book ''Rainbow: The Stormy Life of Judy Garland'' by Christopher Finch. It originally aired on ''[[The NBC Monday Movie|NBC Monday Night at the Movies]]'' on November 6, 1978. The casting of McArdle as Judy Garland was heavily criticized at the time, as the actress did not resemble nor sound remotely like Garland.\n\n==Synopsis==\nThe early life and struggles of Judy Garland during her early years in [[vaudeville]], and follows her through her illustrious and highly-publicized rise to stardom at [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]] studios; her trials as a youngster in dealing with the movie studio system that held her back while her mother was forever pushing her to excel, as well as all the backstage joy and heartbreak during the filming of ''[[The Wizard of Oz (1939 film)|The Wizard of Oz]]'' (1939).\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Andrea McArdle]] as [[Judy Garland]]\n*[[Don Murray (actor)|Don Murray]] as Frank Gumm\n*[[Michael Parks]] as [[Roger Edens]]\n*[[Piper Laurie]] as Ethel Gumm\n*[[Rue McClanahan]] as [[Ida Koverman]]\n*[[Jack Carter (comedian)|Jack Carter]] as [[George Jessel (actor)|George Jessel]]\n*[[Nicholas Pryor]] as Bill Gilmore\n*[[Donna Pescow]] as Jimmie Gumm\n*[[Martin Balsam]] as [[Louis B. Mayer]]\n*[[Johnny Doran (actor)|Johnny Doran]] as [[Jackie Cooper]]\n\n==Award==\n'''[[Primetime Emmy Award|Emmy Award]]'''\n* 1979: [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Cinematography for a Limited Series or Movie|Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Cinematography for a Limited Series or a Special]] \u2013 Howard Schwartz\n\n==External links==\n*{{imdb title|id=0078136|title=Rainbow}}\n*{{tcmdb title|20167|Rainbow}}\n\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Judy Garland]]\n[[Category:1978 television films]]\n[[Category:1970s biographical drama films]]\n[[Category:1970s musical drama films]]\n[[Category:American biographical drama films]]\n[[Category:American musical drama films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:Biographical television films]]\n[[Category:NBC network original films]]\n[[Category:Films based on biographies]]\n[[Category:Films set in the 1920s]]\n[[Category:Films set in the 1930s]]\n[[Category:Films about actors]]\n[[Category:Films about singers]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Jackie Cooper]]\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Rainbow\n| image                = \n| caption              = \n| genre                = Biography<br>Drama<br>Music\n| based_on             = ''Rainbow: The Stormy Life of Judy Garland'' by Christopher Finch\n| writer               = [[John McGreevey]]\n| director             = [[Jackie Cooper]]\n| starring             = [[Andrea McArdle]]<br>[[Don Murray (actor)|Don Murray]]<br>[[Michael Parks]]<br>[[Piper Laurie]]<br>[[Rue McClanahan]]\n| music                = [[Charles Fox (composer)|Charles Fox]]\n| country              = United States\n| language             = English\n| executive_producer   = Greg Strangis<br>[[William Hogan (author)|William Hogan]]\n| producer             = Peter Dunne\n| editor               = Jerry Dronsky\n| cinematography       = Howard Schwartz\n| location             = \n| runtime              = 97 minutes\n| company              = Ten-Four Productions\n| distributor          = [[NBC]]\n| network              = NBC\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|1978|11|06}}\n| website              = \n}}\n'''''Rainbow''''' is a 1978 American [[television film|made-for-television]] [[biographical film|biographical]] [[drama (film and television)|drama film]] which chronicles the early years of singer-actress [[Judy Garland]], portrayed by [[Andrea McArdle]]. Directed by [[Jackie Cooper]], it was written by [[John McGreevey]] based on the 1975 book ''Rainbow: The Stormy Life of Judy Garland'' by Christopher Finch. It originally aired on ''[[The NBC Monday Movie|NBC Monday Night at the Movies]]'' on November 6, 1978. The casting of McArdle as Judy Garland was heavily criticized at the time, as the actress did not resemble nor sound remotely like Garland.\n\n==Synopsis==\nThe early life and struggles of Judy Garland during her early years in [[vaudeville]], and follows her through her illustrious and highly-publicized rise to stardom at [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]] studios; her trials as a youngster in dealing with the movie studio system that held her back while her mother was forever pushing her to excel, as well as all the backstage joy and heartbreak during the filming of ''[[The Wizard of Oz (1939 film)|The Wizard of Oz]]'' (1939).\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Andrea McArdle]] as [[Judy Garland]]\n*[[Don Murray (actor)|Don Murray]] as Frank Gumm\n*[[Michael Parks]] as [[Roger Edens]]\n*[[Piper Laurie]] as Ethel Gumm\n*[[Rue McClanahan]] as [[Ida Koverman]]\n*[[Jack Carter (comedian)|Jack Carter]] as [[George Jessel (actor)|George Jessel]]\n*[[Nicholas Pryor]] as Bill Gilmore\n*[[Donna Pescow]] as Jimmie Gumm\n*[[Martin Balsam]] as [[Louis B. Mayer]]\n*[[Johnny Doran (actor)|Johnny Doran]] as [[Jackie Cooper]]\n\n==Award==\n'''[[Primetime Emmy Award|Emmy Award]]'''\n* 1979: [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Cinematography for a Limited Series or Movie|Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Cinematography for a Limited Series or a Special]] \u2013 Howard Schwartz\n\n==External links==\n*{{imdb title|id=0078136|title=Rainbow}}\n*{{tcmdb title|20167|Rainbow}}\n\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Judy Garland]]\n[[Category:1978 television films]]\n[[Category:1970s biographical drama films]]\n[[Category:1970s musical drama films]]\n[[Category:American biographical drama films]]\n[[Category:American musical drama films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:Biographical television films]]\n[[Category:NBC network original films]]\n[[Category:Films based on biographies]]\n[[Category:Films set in the 1920s]]\n[[Category:Films set in the 1930s]]\n[[Category:Films about actors]]\n[[Category:Films about singers]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Jackie Cooper]]\n", "name_user": "Moe1810", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rainbow_(1978_film)"}
